.TH zola 1  "zola 0.22.1" 
.SH NAME
zola \- A fast static site generator with everything built\-in
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBzola\fR [\fB\-r\fR|\fB\-\-root\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-config\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
A fast static site generator with everything built\-in
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-root\fR \fI<ROOT>\fR [default: .]
Directory to use as root of project
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fI<CONFIG>\fR
Path to a config file other than zola.toml or config.toml in the root of project
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
zola\-init(1)
Create a new Zola project
.TP
zola\-build(1)
Deletes the output directory if there is one and builds the site
.TP
zola\-serve(1)
Serve the site. Rebuild and reload on change automatically
.TP
zola\-check(1)
Try to build the project without rendering it. Checks links
.TP
zola\-completion(1)
Generate shell completion
